{{index}}. {{error_message}}
{{/each}}

Re-run /tmux:task-plan-discover to regenerate discovery outputs, or edit the files manually.

substep.template:
Domain layer goals generated: {{domain_goal_count}}/{{bc_count}} BCs
  - Multi-aggregate BCs (fan-out): {{multi_aggregate_bc_names}}
  - Single-aggregate BCs: {{single_aggregate_bc_names}}
  - Share type ownership: {{share_ownership_summary}}
  - Goal IDs: goal-003 through goal-{{last_domain_goal_id}}
  - All depend on goal-002 (scaffold)

Application layer goals created: {{SUCCESS_COUNT}}/{{BC_COUNT}} BCs
{{#each created}}
  - {{bc_name}}: goal-{{id}} ({{handler_count}} handlers, depends_on=goal-{{domain_id}})
{{/each}}
{{#if failures}}
Failed BCs: {{#each failures}}{{bc_name}} ({{reason}}){{/each}}
{{/if}}

substep.section:
Auth bootstrap goal — the single deterministic owner of authentication infrastructure for the project.
Owns config/packages/security.yaml (firewall, provider, authenticator) and the User entity with password hashing (bcrypt/argon2).
{{#uses_jwt}}Uses lexik/jwt-authentication-bundle as the JWT identity provider; generates the signing keypair.{{/uses_jwt}}
{{^uses_jwt}}Uses the Symfony session/form-login authenticator.{{/uses_jwt}}
See docs/architecture/cross-cutting.md for auth method decisions. See docs/architecture/test-environment.md for test user credentials — never hard-code credentials.

params.param:
[
            "test -f config/packages/security.yaml",
            "vendor/bin/phpstan analyse src/ --level=9",
            "vendor/bin/ecs check src/",
            "vendor/bin/deptrac analyse"
          ]{{#uses_jwt}} plus "bin/console lexik:jwt:check-config"{{/uses_jwt}}

[
            {name: "Seed command run", type: "command-run", paths: ["src/"], commands: ["bin/console app:seed-admin --env=dev", "bin/console app:seed-admin --env=dev"], pass: "Command exits 0 on first AND second run (idempotent), and an admin row is present in the dev database afterward", fail: "Non-zero exit, duplicate admin row, or no admin row after the run"},
            {name: "No inlined secret", type: "file-check", paths: ["src/"], commands: ["grep -rn 'app:seed-admin' src/ to locate the command class, then confirm it reads admin_identifier_env and admin_password_env via getenv/$_ENV and contains NO literal password/secret value"], pass: "Credentials referenced by env-var name only (admin_identifier_env / admin_password_env); no literal secret value in source", fail: "A literal credential value is hardcoded in the command or related source"}
          ]

[
            {name: "Layer Structure Verifier", type: "architecture-check", paths: ["src/"], commands: ["vendor/bin/deptrac analyse", "vendor/bin/deptrac analyse --formatter=json"], pass: "Exit 0, zero violations — all 4 DDD layers (Domain, Application, Infrastructure, Share) respect dependency rules", fail: "Any layer violation detected — dependency flows upward or crosses BC boundary"},
            {name: "Cross-BC Boundary Checker", type: "architecture-check", paths: ["src/"], commands: ["vendor/bin/deptrac analyse --filter=cross-bc", "per-BC grep for cross-BC use-imports inside each Domain layer, excluding Share and the same BC namespace"], pass: "Zero cross-BC imports in Domain/Application layers; only ACL adapters in Infrastructure cross BC boundaries", fail: "Direct cross-BC import found outside ACL adapter"}
          ]

[
              {name: "Full Suite Runner", type: "test-execution", paths: ["tests/"], commands: ["npx playwright test"], pass: "Exit 0, all E2E tests green when run as a single suite — no failures from shared state or missing fixtures", fail: "Any test failure when run together that passed in isolation"},
              {name: "Isolation Checker", type: "test-execution", paths: ["tests/"], commands: ["npx playwright test --shard=random"], pass: "Exit 0, all tests pass in randomized order — no order-dependent failures", fail: "Test failure in randomized order indicates shared mutable state between tests"}
            ]

[
            {name: "Static Analysis Verifier", type: "quality-gate", paths: ["src/"], commands: ["vendor/bin/phpstan analyse src/ --level=9", "vendor/bin/ecs check src/"], pass: "Both exit 0 — zero PHPStan errors at level 9, zero ECS violations", fail: "Any static analysis error or coding standard violation"},
            {name: "Test Suite Runner", type: "test-execution", paths: ["tests/"], commands: ["vendor/bin/phpunit --testsuite=unit", "vendor/bin/phpunit --testsuite=integration", "vendor/bin/phpunit --coverage-text"], pass: "All suites green, coverage meets threshold (default 80%)", fail: "Test failure or coverage below threshold"},
            {name: "Runtime Health Checker", type: "environment-check", paths: ["src/"], commands: ["bin/console", "bin/console doctrine:schema:validate", "bin/console doctrine:migrations:status", "grep for TODO/FIXME/HACK comments in src/ (expect zero)"], pass: "Console boots, schema valid, no pending migrations, zero TODO/FIXME/HACK", fail: "Boot failure, schema mismatch, pending migrations, or stale comments found"}
          ]
